The United States is changing the rules for obtaining a visa
The persons must present themselves before their call at the consulate to the visa services; costs will be reduced in such a way as to reduce waiting times.
As of 10 January 2011, the procedures for applying for visas in the United States Embassy and in the Consulates shall be amended.
In the new procedure, most applicants must present themselves at the visa application service offices (ASC, the initial letter in English) prior to their consultation in the consulate.
The staff of the ASC shall record the biometric data of the applicant, which shall be reviewed by the Consulate prior to the interview.
The new procedure has certain advantages for the aspirants, including:
The total cost of processing the visa is reduced, as it is no longer necessary to pay the appointment, processing the visa application and the transport service with which the document is handed out separately.
The applicant shall make only one payment covering the three services.
The current price remains unchanged: the return to 140 dollars for a tourist visa, 150 dollars for visas with a request (including visas for temporary workers) and 390 dollars for hands and investors.
Those who only want to extend their visas do not have to have a conversation in the consulate, they only have to introduce themselves to the nearest ASC, where they present their documents and take their fingerprints.
As the biometric data are collected in the ASC, the applicants who need a second date for the consultation in the Consulate will have less time there than before.
Those who apply for the visa in the consulates of Ciudad Chihuahua, Monterrey and Nuevo Laredo will no longer have to pay the service charge of 26 dollars.
For more information about the new visa application process, please visit the following website: http://mexico.usembassy.gov/boletines/sp100201_Visas-FAQs.html
